               <head>Islamic eschatology</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Mawlavī ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85043040 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85070921" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16782-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on signs and events of the Last Day according to Islamic eschatology, entitled <title>Tarjumah-'i ishāʿah-'i ʿalāmat al-sāʿah</title>.
Another autograph manuscript of the Afghan scholar Mawlavī ‘Abd al-Ḥaqq. This text too appears never to have been published.
                        </p>
                        <p>The main text is preceded on 1v-4v by a text commenting on Qur’ānic verses concerning the creation of the heavens and earth, and followed on 70r-v by a table of contents.</p>
                        <p>Autograph. Colophon on f. 69v. Completed on 8 Shavvāl/23 Jady 1313/12 January 1934. </p>
                        <p>Cursive quasi-naskhī. 23-33 lines. Paginated: 136, [2] p. 70 folios. 20 x 16 cm. Boards faced with paper having a green pattern on white background; red leather spine and corners.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from Mr. N. Madjnun, 8 January 2010. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7272">Mawlavī ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq</persName>
                        <persName key="person_f7272" xml:lang="per">مولوى عبد الحقّ</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
